01/03/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia's Constitutional Court announced that it expects an official notification from the government concerning President Boris Trajkovski's death in order to terminate his mandate, <I>Utrinski Vesnik</I> reported Monday (1 March).Once notification is received, the court will be able to start procedures for organising the election of a new president. Under those procedures, Parliamentary Speaker and acting President Ljupco Jordanovski will determine an election date and then immediately appoint the chairman and members of State Electoral Commission. The political parties will then have 15 days to present their candidates to run in the presidential race. (Utrinski Vesnik - 01/03/04)
